{
  "page": "Maiden's Bane",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Longship_Maiden%27s_Bane_Tomasz_Jedruszek.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/49/Longship_Maiden%27s_Bane_Tomasz_Jedruszek.png/400px-Longship_Maiden%27s_Bane_Tomasz_Jedruszek.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"256\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/4/49/Longship_Maiden%27s_Bane_Tomasz_Jedruszek.png 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Longship_Maiden%27s_Bane_Tomasz_Jedruszek.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Longship <i>Maiden's Bane</i>. © FFG</div></div></div>\n<p><i><b>Maiden's Bane</b></i> is an <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> longship and part of the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Fleet\" title=\"Iron Fleet\">Iron Fleet</a>. It may be named after King <a href=\"/index.php/Joron_I_Blacktyde\" title=\"Joron I Blacktyde\">Joron I Blacktyde</a>, who was known as Maidensbane.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maiden%27s_Bane&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maiden%27s_Bane&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>After the <a href=\"/index.php/Taking_of_the_Shields\" title=\"Taking of the Shields\">taking of the Shields</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Victarion_Greyjoy\" title=\"Victarion Greyjoy\">Victarion Greyjoy</a> keeps <i>Maiden's Bane</i>, <i><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Dagon\" title=\"Lord Dagon\">Lord Dagon</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Wind\" title=\"Iron Wind\">Iron Wind</a></i>, and <i><a href=\"/index.php/Grief_(ship)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Grief (ship)\">Grief</a></i> as part of his rearguard, commanding from his own ship, <i><a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Victory\" title=\"Iron Victory\">Iron Victory</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maiden%27s_Bane&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><i>Maiden's Bane</i> appears three days prior to Victarion's departure from the <a href=\"/index.php/Isle_of_Cedars\" title=\"Isle of Cedars\">Isle of Cedars</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maiden%27s_Bane&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Iron Islands: Driftwood Crowns.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_29\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 29\">Chapter 29</a>, The Reaver.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_